RDS Proxy
    Amazon RDS Proxy is a fully managed service from Amazon RDS that sits between your application and the database. 
    Its main job is to manage and reuse database connections efficiently so the database is not overloaded with too many connections.


Running a database on an EC2 instance means you install and manage the database yourself on a virtual server provided by Amazon EC2.

When companies use DB on EC2

    Need full database control
    
    Custom database configuration
    
    Unsupported engines in RDS
    
    Cost optimization in some cases
